[2] _Aedes albopictus_ positive
Date: 4 Sep 2007
From:Dr. Michele Dottori
<michele.dottori@bs.izs.it>

Chikungunya virus infection has been confirmed in _Aedes albopictus_
captured in Castiglione di Cervia, a village in the province of
Ravenna, Italy, where an outbreak of the disease involved more than
150 people since mid July 2007. The insects were captured by experts
of Centro Agricoltura e Ambiente in Crevalcore in collaboration with
the Health Department of Ravenna. The viral RNA has been detected by
2 different PCR protocols (RT-nPCR proposed by Pffefer et al. in J.
Vet. Med. B. 49,49-54, 2002, and a Real Time PCR Taqman proposed by
Pastorino et al. in J. Virol. Methods 124, 2005 65-71) in the Reggio
Emilia Unit of Istituto Zooprofilattico della Lombardia e dell'
Emilia Romagna. Attempts at viral isolation and sequencing of the
viral genome amplified by PCR are ongoing at the laboratories of the
same institute in Brescia.
--
Dr. Michele Dottori
Istituto Zooprofilattico Lombardia e dell' Emilia Romagna
Sezione Diagnostica di Reggio Emilia
Reggio Emilia, Italy
<michele.dottori@bs.izs.it>
